All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Administrator
The Administrator class provides the functionality for an administrator to manage various operations in a hospital system, including staff management, appointments, medication inventory, and replenishment requests.
AppointmentManager
The AppointmentManager class provides functionality for managing appointment scheduling, rescheduling, cancellations, and viewing appointments.
AppointmentOutcomeManager
The AppointmentOutcomeManager class manages appointment outcomes, including recording, updating, and viewing outcomes.
AppointmentOutcomeService
The AppointmentOutcomeService interface provides methods for recording and viewing appointment outcomes and past records for patients.
AppointmentSchedulingService
The AppointmentSchedulingService interface provides methods for scheduling, rescheduling, canceling, and managing appointments.
AppointmentSlotManager
The AppointmentSlotManager class provides functionality for managing appointment slots, including updating availability, creating new slots, and viewing available slots.
AppointmentSlotService
The AppointmentSlotService interface provides methods for managing appointment slots, including updating availability, creating new slots, and viewing available slots.
ConsoleLogger
The ConsoleLogger class implements the Logger interface, providing logging functionality that outputs messages to the console.
CsvFileReader
The CsvFileReader class provides methods to read data from CSV files located in the resources folder.
CsvFileWriter
The CsvFileWriter class provides methods to write or modify data in CSV files located within the project structure.
DataProcessor
The DataProcessor class provides methods for reading, writing, updating, and deleting data from CSV files.
dataReader
The dataReader interface defines methods for reading data from a CSV file.
dataWriter
The dataWriter interface defines methods for writing data to a CSV file.
DispensingService
The DispensingService interface provides methods for dispensing items in an inventory system.
Doctor
Represents a Doctor in the hospital management system.
DoctorMedicalRecordManager
The DoctorMedicalRecordManager class provides methods for viewing and updating medical records in the system.
FileLogger
The FileLogger class implements the Logger interface and provides functionality for logging messages to a file.
hospitalStaffManagement
The hospitalStaffManagement class implements the StaffManagementAdd, StaffManagementUpdate, StaffManagementRemove, and StaffManagementView interfaces, providing functionality for managing hospital staff records.
InventoryManagement
The InventoryManagement class provides comprehensive functionality for managing inventory items, including viewing, submitting replenishment requests, restocking, and handling pending requests.
Logger
The Logger interface defines the basic structure for logging messages to a destination.
LoggingManager
Manages logging operations by delegating them to a specific Logger instance.
MedicalRecordManagement
The MedicalRecordManagement class serves as a high-level module for managing medical records.
MedicalRecordService
The MedicalRecordService interface defines the operations for managing medical records.
Patient
The Patient class represents a patient user within the Hospital Management System.
PatientMedicalRecordManager
The PatientMedicalRecordManager class provides functionality for patients to view and update their medical records.
PendingManagement
The PendingManagement interface defines methods for managing items with a pending status.
Pharmacist
Represents a Pharmacist in the medical management system.
PrescriptionManagement
The PrescriptionManagement class handles dispensing and approval of prescriptions.
ReplenishmentService
The ReplenishmentService interface provides methods for managing inventory replenishment.
StaffFilter
The StaffFilter interface defines a contract for filtering staff data.
StaffManagementAdd
The StaffManagementAdd interface defines the contract for adding new staff records to the hospital management system.
StaffManagementRemove
The StaffManagementRemove interface defines the contract for removing staff records from the hospital management system.
StaffManagementUpdate
The StaffManagementUpdate interface defines the contract for updating staff records in the hospital management system.
StaffManagementView
The StaffManagementView interface defines the contract for viewing and filtering hospital staff records based on specific categories and keywords.
SystemInitialization
The SystemInitialization class serves as the entry point for the Hospital Management System.
userLogin
The userLogin interface defines the contract for a user authentication and management system.
UserLoginServices
Implements userLogin interface for user authentication, registration, and password management.
ViewAppointment
The ViewAppointment interface provides methods for viewing appointments and schedules for both patients and doctors.
